definition: rich/abundant/exuberant/to add for free/to throw in as bonus/to spare/to forgive/despite/although
to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be
bubbling with humor (idiom); witty and interesting

sentences.english: Maybe you can tell your friends are very excitedly discussing an event.
sentences.chinese: 你可能發現你的朋友們饒有興致地談論一個活動。

sentences.english: Capturing such a beautiful moment can be exciting as well as a fun activity.
sentences.chinese: 捕捉到如此美麗的一刻既令人激動，又饒有興味。

sentences.english: NASA followed Stevie’s progress with interest.
sentences.chinese: 國家航空總署饒有興趣地追蹤着史蒂夫此事的進展。

sentences.english: And I read the tabulation of the votes with interest.
sentences.chinese: 我也饒有興致地讀了那些投票組成的那個表格。
阿齊茲饒有興味地注視着他。

sentences.english: He is leisurely drinking by himself in front of his small house.
sentences.chinese: 他饒有閒趣地在自己的小屋前自斟自酌。

sentences.english: After the ruins it is very interesting to peep into the cave settlement.
sentences.chinese: 離開遺址之後，我們饒有興趣地往洞穴裏面看。
皮徹饒有興趣地看着他們。

sentences.english: I hope the next speaker dishes up his arguments in a more interesting manner.
sentences.chinese: 我希望下一個發言人更加饒有風趣地提出他的論點。

sentences.english: There is a Doll House Exhibition on one floor, which is interesting, too.
sentences.chinese: 那裏還有一層，辦了一個迷你屋的展覽，也饒有趣味。

sentences.english: The result is awaited with interest.
sentences.chinese: 人們饒有興味地等待着結果。

sentences.english: All the men eyed the beautiful girl with interest.
sentences.chinese: 所有男人都饒有興趣地盯着看這位美麗的姑娘。

sentences.english: Therefore the 13th Dalai Lama was interesting.
sentences.chinese: 因此，十三世達賴喇嘛是饒有興味的。

sentences.english: Jumping steps in Manipuri dance add interest to dance sequences.
sentences.chinese: 在曼尼普爾舞跳步舞，饒有趣味的序列。

sentences.english: The English language has an interesting history.
sentences.chinese: 輬英語有着饒有趣味的發展歷史。

sentences.english: Started in the Southern Song Dynasty riddles , lively, interesting sense of humor.
sentences.chinese: 始於南宋的燈謎，生動活潑，饒有風趣。
